1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
You can't see a black hole — so how did scientists capture its shadow?

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:11,200
Meet the Event Horizon Telescope—an array of global telescopes acting as one gigantic eye.

3
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:18,000
In 2019, they unveiled the first ever image of a black hole: M87*, showcasing its photon ring.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:24,000
This shadow isn’t the black hole itself, but the light bending around it—a cosmic illusion.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:29,600
The EHT Collaboration's groundbreaking work pushed the boundaries of our understanding of the universe.

6
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,200
Curious about what else we can find in space?

7
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,600
Hit that follow button for more!
